VALUES (1, 'Spaghetti Carbonara', 30, 'spaghetti-carbonara.jpg', 4, 9, 0, 0, 1, 'eggs, bacon, Parmesan cheese, black pepper', '1. Cook spaghetti according to package instructions. 2. In a separate pan, fry the bacon until crispy. 3. In a bowl, whisk together eggs, grated Parmesan cheese, and black pepper. 4. Drain cooked spaghetti and mix with the bacon. 5. Pour the egg mixture over the spaghetti and toss quickly to coat. Serve immediately.');

VALUES (1, 'Homemade Pizza', 45, 'homemade-pizza.jpg', 8, 8, 0, 1, 0, 'flour, yeast, water, tomato sauce, mozzarella cheese, toppings of your choice', '1. Prepare the pizza dough by mixing flour, yeast, and water. Let it rise for an hour. 2. Roll out the dough into a round shape. 3. Spread tomato sauce over the dough, leaving a border around the edges. 4. Sprinkle mozzarella cheese and add your favorite toppings. 5. Bake in a preheated oven at 425°F (220°C) for 15-20 minutes or until the crust is golden and the cheese is melted.');

VALUES (1, 'Chicken Pot Pie', 60, 'chicken-pot-pie.jpg', 6, 7, 0, 0, 0, 'chicken, carrots, peas, onions, puff pastry', '1. Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C). 2. In a saucepan, cook chicken, carrots, peas, and onions until tender. 3. In a separate saucepan, prepare the creamy filling with butter, flour, and milk. 4. Combine the cooked chicken and vegetables with the creamy filling. 5. Pour the mixture into a pie dish and cover with puff pastry. 6. Bake for 30-35 minutes or until the crust is golden brown.');

VALUES (1, 'Chocolate Chip Cookies', 25, 'chocolate-chip-cookies.jpg', 12, 9, 0, 1, 0, 'butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla extract, flour, baking soda, chocolate chips', '1. Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C). 2. In a mixing bowl, cream together butter, sugar, and brown sugar. 3. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. 4. Stir in vanilla extract. 5. In a separate bowl, combine flour and baking soda. Gradually add to the butter mixture. 6. Stir in chocolate chips. 7. Drop rounded tablespoons of dough onto a greased baking sheet. 8. Bake for 9-11 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on wire racks.');

VALUES (5, 'Caesar Salad', 15, 'caesar-salad.jpg', 4, 8, 0, 1, 1, 'romaine lettuce, croutons, Parmesan cheese, Caesar dressing', '1. Tear the romaine lettuce into bite-sized pieces and place in a large bowl. 2. Add croutons and grated Parmesan cheese. 3. Drizzle with Caesar dressing. 4. Toss the salad until well-coated. Serve immediately.');

VALUES (6, 'Beef Stir-Fry', 25, 'beef-stir-fry.jpg', 4, 7, 0, 0, 1, 'beef, broccoli, bell peppers, soy sauce, garlic, ginger', '1. Slice the beef into thin strips. 2. In a hot pan, stir-fry beef until browned. 3. Remove beef from the pan and set aside. 4. Stir-fry broccoli, bell peppers, garlic, and ginger until tender-crisp. 5. Return beef to the pan and add soy sauce. 6. Stir-fry for another minute or until heated through. Serve hot.');

VALUES (7, 'Caprese Salad', 10, 'caprese-salad.jpg', 2, 6, 1, 1, 1, 'tomatoes, mozzarella cheese, fresh basil leaves, balsamic glaze', '1. Slice the tomatoes and mozzarella cheese into thick slices. 2. Arrange them on a plate, alternating between tomato and mozzarella. 3. Tuck fresh basil leaves between the slices. 4. Drizzle with balsamic glaze. Serve immediately.');

VALUES (8, 'Grilled Salmon', 20, 'grilled-salmon.jpg', 2, 9, 0, 1, 1, 'salmon fillets, lemon, olive oil, salt, pepper', '1. Preheat the grill to medium-high heat. 2. Season the salmon fillets with salt, pepper, and a squeeze of lemon juice. 3. Brush the grill grates with olive oil. 4. Place the salmon fillets on the grill, skin-side down. 5. Cook for about 4-6 minutes per side, or until the fish flakes easily with a fork. Serve hot.');

VALUES (9, 'Mushroom Risotto', 40, 'mushroom-risotto.jpg', 6, 7, 1, 1, 1, 'arborio rice, mushrooms, onion, garlic, vegetable broth, Parmesan cheese', '1. In a large pot, heat vegetable broth and keep it simmering. 2. In a separate pan, sauté mushrooms, onion, and garlic until tender. 3. Add arborio rice to the pan and stir for a minute. 4. Gradually add hot vegetable broth, stirring constantly, until absorbed. 5. Continue adding broth and stirring until the rice is creamy and cooked. 6. Stir in grated Parmesan cheese. Serve hot.');

VALUES (10, 'Chicken Parmesan', 45, 'chicken-parmesan.jpg', 4, 8, 0, 0, 0, 'chicken breasts, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, marinara sauce, mozzarella cheese', '1. Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C). 2. Coat chicken breasts in bread crumbs mixed with grated Parmesan cheese. 3. In a hot pan, brown the chicken on both sides. 4. Transfer chicken to a baking dish and cover with marinara sauce and mozzarella cheese. 5. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until the cheese is melted and bubbly. Serve with pasta.');

VALUES (11, 'Shrimp Scampi', 20, 'shrimp-scampi.jpg', 2, 9, 0, 0, 1, 'shrimp, garlic, butter, white wine, lemon juice, parsley', '1. In a hot pan, melt butter and sauté garlic until fragrant. 2. Add shrimp and cook until pink and opaque. 3. Pour in white wine and lemon juice. 4. Cook for another minute or until the sauce thickens slightly. 5. Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Serve hot with pasta or crusty bread.');

VALUES (12, 'Beef Tacos', 30, 'beef-tacos.jpg', 4, 8, 0, 0, 0, 'ground beef, taco seasoning, tortillas, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, salsa', '1. In a skillet, brown ground beef and drain excess fat. 2. Stir in taco seasoning and cook until well combined. 3. Warm tortillas in a separate pan. 4. Fill tortillas with beef, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, and salsa. 5. Fold and serve immediately.');

VALUES (13, 'Vegetable Curry', 35, 'vegetable-curry.jpg', 6, 7, 1, 1, 1, 'assorted vegetables (e.g., carrots, potatoes, bell peppers, cauliflower), curry paste, coconut milk, vegetable broth', '1. In a large pot, heat curry paste and sauté vegetables until slightly tender. 2. Add coconut milk and vegetable broth. 3. Simmer until vegetables are cooked through. 4. Serve hot with rice or naan bread.');

VALUES (14, 'Pasta Primavera', 25, 'pasta-primavera.jpg', 4, 8, 1, 1, 1, 'pasta, assorted vegetables (e.g., broccoli, carrots, zucchini, bell peppers), garlic, olive oil, Parmesan cheese', '1. Cook pasta according to package instructions. 2. In a separate pan, sauté garlic and vegetables in olive oil until crisp-tender. 3. Drain pasta and toss with the sautéed vegetables. 4. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Serve hot.');

VALUES (15, 'Lemon Garlic Roasted Chicken', 50, 'lemon-garlic-roasted-chicken.jpg', 4, 9, 0, 0, 1, 'whole chicken, lemon, garlic, olive oil, salt, pepper, fresh herbs (e.g., rosemary, thyme)', '1. Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C). 2. Rub the chicken with lemon juice, garlic, olive oil, salt, pepper, and fresh herbs. 3. Place the chicken on a roasting pan and roast for about 1 hour or until the internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C). 4. Let it rest for a few minutes before carving. Serve with roasted vegetables.');

VALUES (16, 'Fish Tacos', 30, 'fish-tacos.jpg', 4, 7, 0, 1, 1, 'white fish fillets, flour, cornmeal, spices, tortillas, cabbage, lime crema', '1. In a shallow dish, combine flour, cornmeal, and spices. 2. Dredge fish fillets in the flour mixture. 3. Heat oil in a pan and cook fish until crispy and golden brown. 4. Warm tortillas in a separate pan. 5. Fill tortillas with fish, shredded cabbage, and lime crema. Serve with lime wedges.');

VALUES (17, 'Homemade Pizza', 40, 'homemade-pizza.jpg', 8, 8, 0, 1, 0, 'pizza dough, marinara sauce, mozzarella cheese, assorted toppings (e.g., pepperoni, mushrooms, bell peppers, onions)', '1. Preheat the oven to 475°F (245°C). 2. Roll out the pizza dough and place it on a baking sheet or pizza stone. 3. Spread marinara sauce on the dough and sprinkle with mozzarella cheese. 4. Add your desired toppings. 5. Bake for 12-15 minutes or until the crust is golden and the cheese is bubbly. Slice and serve hot.');

VALUES (18, 'Chicken Noodle Soup', 60, 'chicken-noodle-soup.jpg', 6, 9, 0, 0, 0, 'chicken, noodles, carrots, celery, onion, garlic, chicken broth, herbs', '1. In a large pot, cook chicken until no longer pink. Remove from pot and shred. 2. In the same pot, sauté carrots, celery, onion, and garlic until softened. 3. Add chicken broth, shredded chicken, and herbs. 4. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes. 5. Add noodles and cook until tender. Serve hot.');

VALUES (19, 'Egg Fried Rice', 20, 'egg-fried-rice.jpg', 4, 7, 0, 1, 0, 'cooked rice, eggs, carrots, peas, soy sauce, sesame oil, green onions', '1. Heat oil in a pan and scramble the eggs. Set aside. 2. In the same pan, sauté carrots and peas until tender. 3. Add cooked rice and stir-fry until heated through. 4. Drizzle with soy sauce and sesame oil. 5. Stir in scrambled eggs and chopped green onions. Serve hot.');

VALUES (20, 'Mediterranean Salad', 15, 'mediterranean-salad.jpg', 2, 7, 1, 1, 1, 'lettuce, tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, olives, feta cheese, lemon juice, olive oil, herbs', '1. In a large bowl, combine lettuce, tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, olives, and crumbled feta cheese. 2. In a separate small bowl, whisk together lemon juice, olive oil, and herbs to make the dressing. 3. Pour the dressing over the salad and toss to coat. Serve chilled.');


